The paper discusses the normalization of citation impact, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely sub-category as it deals with bibliometrics and citation analysis. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as it deals with the retrieval and analysis of information from large datasets, including citation data. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also possible as they deal with data analysis and network analysis, which are relevant to citation impact normalization. Finally, cs.DB (Databases) is a possible sub-category as it deals with the organization and management of large datasets, including citation data.
